  <div class="two-col">
    <div>
      <p class="body-text lede">Most people building with AI agents are either business operators who use off-the-shelf tools, or engineers who build technically impressive demos disconnected from revenue.</p>
      <p class="body-text">Saad is doing both simultaneously — and the two sides feed each other. The RevOps background means every technical decision maps to a business outcome. The engineering means he doesn't just spec what agents should do — he builds the skills, wires the MCPs, deploys the infrastructure, and debugs at 2am when something breaks.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="pull-quote-tegaki">
        <tegaki-renderer class="tegaki-pull" font="Caveat" speed="1.8" loop>AI agents need infrastructure that mirrors human business operations — email, scheduling, browser access, phone calls, CRM, team coordination.</tegaki-renderer>
        <div class="attrib">— The Thesis</div>
      </div>
      <p class="body-text">Saad is building that infrastructure layer by layer, skill by skill, in production. The current focus: <strong>AgenticMail</strong>, <strong>Klaus/Kurausu</strong>, and <strong>Uptime</strong> — an AI-driven freight tech platform born from 5 years of domain expertise at KeepTruckin.</p>
